  "prompt": "Can I deposit cash without cheque in SBI?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deposit cash without a cheque in your State Bank of India (SBI) account. You typically have a few options to do this:\n\n1. **Branch Visit**: You can visit any SBI branch and fill out a deposit slip for cash deposit. Ensure you have your account number handy. The bank teller will process your deposit.\n\n2. **Cash Deposit Machine (CDM)**: SBI provides Cash Deposit Machines where you can deposit cash directly into your account. You'll need your debit card for identification or sometimes just entering the account number is sufficient. Follow the instructions on the machine to complete your deposit.\n\n3. **YONO Cash**: Using the SBI YONO app, you can avail the YONO Cash service at ATMs or CDMs, though this usually involves withdrawal rather than deposit.\n\nAlways ensure that you receive a receipt for your transaction, especially when dealing with cash deposits at a branch or via a machine.",
